"The maximum leave of absence for Guangxi University students to start a business can be up to 5 years- Xinhua News."
"Xinhua News, Naning, May 19th (Reporter Zhang Yin): Reporters recently learned from the Education Department of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region that in the future, colleges and universities in Guangxi will implement flexible educational systems, relax the leave of absence for university students, and extend the leave of absence for students who are in school for entrepreneurship by 2 to 5 years on the basis of the original educational system. The leave of absence for entrepreneurship can be considered as practical education time."
"In order to promote the enhancement of university students' entrepreneurship and innovation ability, departments such as education and human resources in Guangxi work together to build entrepreneurship platforms, construct more off-campus practical teaching bases, university science and technology parks, university student entrepreneurship parks, and entrepreneurial incubation bases for university students, providing external protection for their entrepreneurship."
"According to the requirements, by 2020, the area of innovation and entrepreneurship practice bases of each college and university should reach more than 3,000 square meters for undergraduate schools and more than 2,000 square meters for vocational schools."
"The government encourages colleges and universities to establish innovation and entrepreneurship credits, and prioritizes supporting students who perform exceptionally well in innovation and entrepreneurship practices to change their major."
"College teachers must be assigned to work in industrial enterprises for at least two months every two years to improve their awareness and ability in innovation and entrepreneurship education."
"The education bureau of the autonomous region requires all colleges and universities in Guangxi to deeply implement the university students' innovation and entrepreneurship training plan, striving to ensure that every university student participates in one innovation and entrepreneurship training plan during their school years."
"Colleges and universities should actively organize students to participate in various innovation and entrepreneurship competitions at all levels, and provide financial support."